    "text": "Erdős Problem #852: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. Let $d_n=p_{n+1}-p_n$, where $p_n$ is the $n$th prime. Let $h(x)$ be maximal such that for some $n<x$ the numbers $d_n,d_{n+1},\\ldots,d_{n+h(x)-1}$ are all distinct. Estimate $h(x)$. In particular, is it true that\\[h(x) >(\\log x)^c\\]for some constant $c>0$, and\\[h(x)=o(\\log x)?\\] Prize: no. OEIS: A001223, A053597, A078515. Tags: number theory, primes.",
